      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask for the patient's full mailing address.\n\nSay something like: \"And what's your current address? \nWe'll need the full thing — street, city, state, and \nzip code.\"\n\nIf the user gives a partial address (e.g. just the \nstreet or city), ask for the rest: \"Got it — and \nwhat's the city, state, and zip?\"\n\nIf the user gives everything at once, read back the \nfull address to confirm: \"Let me make sure I have \nthat right — [full address]. Is that correct?\"\n\nIf the user gives a PO Box: Accept it but ask: \"We \ncan use the PO Box for mail, but the clinic may also \nneed a physical address for insurance verification. \nDo you have one you can share?\"\n\nIf the user is unsure why we need it: \"The clinic \nneeds it for insurance verification and to have on \nfile for your records. It's standard for all new \npatients.\"\n\nDo NOT ask more than twice."
      }
    },
